{
  "rule": "weno5_advection_2d",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "expected_min_order": 4.5,
  "notes": "Classical Jiang-Shu (1996) WENO5 nonlinear reconstruction applied dimension-by-dimension on a uniform 2D structured Cartesian grid is theoretically O(h^5) in L_inf for smooth solutions (Shu 1998 §2.2; LeVeque 2002 §20). The 4.5 floor sub-5th formal order accounts for the small accuracy hit from the nonlinear-weight recovery of linear weights (omega_k -> d_k) at finite eps = 1e-6 plus the per-axis weight-transition coupling that lowers the asymptotic order vs the 1D fixture (which uses 4.7 — see weno5_advection/fixtures/convergence/expected.esm). The sweep is driven by ESS's `mms_weno5_convergence` 2D dispatch (esm-hsa): the harness applies the rule's `axes.x` 1D sub-stencil row-wise on the cell-averaged separable manufactured solution `phase_shifted_sine_product_2d` and compares against the perpendicular-axis-averaged analytic face value. WENO5's positive homogeneity makes the result symmetric in x↔y; verifying one axis is sufficient for the asymptotic order claim."
}
